node.text:
Since founding @tableau_cph, his “gallery for flowers,” four years ago, Julius Værnes Iversen has become Danish fashion’s go-to floral designer, known for his artful floral installations. He created one of these for the @cphfw presentation of @the.garment, a new, sustainable label founded and designed by @sophiaroe and @charlotte_eskildsen.  Click the link in bio to read more about Tableau. 
video by @frederikke.norgard

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue Runway on August 18, 2021 tagging @jamesveloria, @toddoldham, and @veronicawebb. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: This Thursday, @jameveloria—the not-so-hidden vintage gem located on the second floor of a modest Chinatown mall—will transform into a buyable museum packed with Todd Oldham runway pieces. The shop has curated designer-specific sales before, including for Tom Ford–era Gucci and Vivienne Westwood, but the Oldham factor was serendipitous. The designer’s nephew, jewelry designer @presley.oldham, had been coming into the store for years to shop and sell and convinced his uncle to do something with his archive. Tap the link in bio for a glimpse of what will be available—and expect a long line of eager customers.

node.text: Suiting was a major component of Scandi-chic style before the pandemic, and it was amazing to see how quickly designers returned to tailoring at Copenhagen Fashion Week this season. Tap the link in bio for the best suits by @mkdtstudio, @stinegoya, @brogger, and more, plus @the_lbp's full trend report from Copenhagen.

node.text: How do you immortalize @chloesevigny, the perpetually coolest girl in New York? Easy. Put her on a T-shirt. That very garment is one of the standout pieces from her latest collaboration with New York-based streetwear label @richardsonworld. The capsule is a flirty workwear dream, including a black canvas jacket, a pleated skirt in both black and white, and two tees (short- and long-sleeved) emblazoned with a black and white photograph of the actor as a euphoric, partying city kid. Tap the link in bio for more about the collection.

node.text: No one understands transformation better than @madonna. The music icon, who turns 63 today, forged a symbiotic relationship with the fashion community the moment she burst onto the scene in the ’80s, setting trends and playing muse to countless designers. Tap the link in bio for a look back at her very best moments in Vogue. Photographed by Steven Meisel, Vogue, October 1992

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vogue Runway on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and purse.

node.text: “Heels should be able to be worn by anyone that wants to,” says @markbryan911, the cis, straight male engineer who has gained a cult following on Instagram for his love of sky-high heels. Vogue reached out to Bryan and more heel lovers to ask not only where they shop, but  what it means to them to rock heels on the streets. Tap the link in bio for the full story.

node.text: Busy summer weekends require the ease and functionality of a hands-free crossbody bag. Tap the link in bio to shop the very best ones right now by Khaite, JW Pei, Medea, and more. Photographed by @EthanJamesGreen, Vogue, May 2020

node.text: There’s no surprise that sun-kissed Cali girl Kaia Gerber has earmarked one of @shopdoen's effortless minis as her dress of the summer. Gerber paired the dress with white tennis sneakers showing us just how easy summer dressing can be. Tap the link in bio to shop the dress of the summer.

node.text: The September issue offers a first glimpse inside the new exhibition on American fashion at the Metropolitan Museum of Art. Tap the link in bio to take a peek behind the curtain and see a few of the featured looks by @marcjacobs, @ralphlauren, and more. Photographed by @StefanRuizphoto, styled by @gurvial, Vogue, September 2021

node.text:
In a portfolio shared across 27 editions of Vogue around the world, 19 models flaunt 35 looks from the fall collections; their styles ranging from the smartly subdued to the go-for-broke glamorous. Representing both the U.S. and the U.K., fashion editors Camilla Nickerson, @Alex_Jordan_Harrington, Poppy Kain, and Julia Sarr-Jamois led the effort, thinking along four broad aesthetic lines: the short and bright, inventive approaches to leather, reimagined florals, and bold spins on knitwear. Click the link in our bio to take in the joyous results.
Photographed by @Studio_Jackson and styled by @Alex_Jordan_Harrington, @PoppyKain, Camilla Nickerson and @SarrJamois, Vogue, September 2021.

node.text: @sakspotts showed its fall 2021 collection the yard of the home Arne Jacobsen, the Functionalist Danish architect and inventor of the Egg chair, built for himself around 1930. The Bauhaus-style house he designed for himself is a clean-lined, white-painted, minimal box. It was here that Cathrine Saks and Barbara Potts revealed their collection and their new direction. See more at the link in bio. Video by @styledumonde

node.text: A slice of the Big Apple is coming to Copenhagen, served up in the form of a monographic exhibition, “My Paper World,” featuring the work of @phoebenewyork at the Horsens Art Museum. Opening on the heels of Copenhagen Fashion Week, the show runs from August 21, 2021, through January 30, 2022 and brings the popular collaged street art to a museum setting for the first time. Read more at the link in bio.
